rComments: Great lecturer, but could be better organized. Very sharp and clear requirements, focused, able to deliver course material effectively and makes everything more interesting than it deserves to be. All in all, great learning experience. Can be a bit tough on tests.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: This professor was excellent! He was extremely approachable and helpful in his emails and office hours. His slides weren't of much use during his lectures but the lectures themselves were very informative. The primary source readings he assigned were always enjoyable  for readings. Textbook material was covered in class, but very informative.

The professor is useful and his TAs seem to be invested in the course. His powerpoint could use use but his lectures were clear and went pretty slow so if you're unfamiliar with the material, don't fear. Would recommend for EAS or any history student.
He's alright. Knows Korea well. Load - you have to read what is assigned, otherwise will be burned. Good luck.

Professor Schmid is definitely one to be remembered. He's helpful, patient, and understanding. The workload was heavy but like all courses at U of T, it is manageable. He's outdone himself in the seminar course, as he essentially enabled students to hone their research and writing skills. Put in the effort and you'll get your desired mark!

Really fantastic prof. Had him in my second year and I still remember how proud I was to have done well in his class. He made learning about the colonial period in Korea so fascinating and examined difficult theoretical concepts very succinctly. I would've loved to take another one of his classes.

Great prof. Certainly one of the best in the EAS department. You can learn a lot from him and he always has an interesting story to tell along with his lectures. Also a very nice guy, 100% approachable.
He's very understanding, helpful and nice~ very knowledgeable, I learned a lot in his class.  A great professor indeed.

He simply is the BEST prof/teacher i've ever had during my 5 years at UofT! He is professional, knowledgeable, passionate, stimulating, encouraging, and inspirational. He is attentive to students' needs. He is approachable. He gives feedback promptly. I learned a lot from him. He makes learning fun and interesting!
He is SOOOO Cute. I spent the whole class watching him.

great prof, one of the best i've had so far.  knowledgable, lectures well, and shows great enthusiasm for course material.  i don't know what the previous post was talking about, he's not mean and replies to e-mails with very reasonable promptness and has accomodating office hours.
he's so mean. He doesn't even reply emails, and he doesn't want to help at all.
very nice guy
Prof. Schmid is always sensitive, informative and supportive. I absolutely adore him! He's such a cutie!

I love Prof. Schmid!  He was such a great lecturer and used lots of multimedia to keep us entertained!  And his points were made more interesting (and therefore more memorable) by occasionally adding personal tidbits.  A+!
